Place beef in 3 1/2 to 4-quart slow cooker (discard seasoning packet). Add peppercorns and bay leaf. Add enough water to cover brisket. Cover and cook on Low 6 to 7 hours or until tender. Set oven control to broil. Remove cooked brisket from slow cooker. Place fat side up on broiler pan. Cover with brown sugar. Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat 3 to 4 minutes or until sugar is melted and crusty. Meanwhile, prepare gravy as directed on package. Stir in mustard. Serve gravy with brisket.